  "text": "Accumulated nitrite (NO 2 − ), an index of cell-released NO, in conditioned media was quantitated using a spectrophotometric assay based upon Griess reaction [CITATION_1] . In brief, an equal volume of Griess reagent (1% sulfanilamide -0.1% N-1-naphthyl-ethylenediamine dihydrochloride in 2.5% phosphoric acid) was incubated with conditioned medium for 10 min at room temperature, and then the absorbance at 550 nm was measured using a microplate reader (SpectraMax iD3 Multi-Mode, Molecular Devices, USA). The calibration curve was constructed using known concentrations (0−160 μM) of sodium nitrite.",
